about.summary: CMake is an extensible, open-source system that manages the build process

name: cmake
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "3.12.0" %}

package:
  name: cmake
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/-/archive/v{{ version }}/cmake-v{{ version }}.tar.bz2
  fn: cmake-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 461dd6b49d636a044f65efcec0be2f448e531d3ac593966944407c3198bbb334

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [win and vc<14]
  ignore_run_exports:
    - vc

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}

  host:
    - bzip2           # [unix]
    - curl            # [unix]
    - expat           # [unix]
    - ncurses         # [unix]
    - xz              # [unix]
    - zlib            # [unix]
    - libuv           # [unix]
    - rhash           # [unix]

  run:
    - bzip2           # [unix]
    - curl            # [unix]
    - expat           # [unix]
    - ncurses         # [unix]
    - xz              # [unix]
    - zlib            # [unix]
    - libuv           # [unix]
    - rhash           # [unix]
    - vs2015_runtime  # [win]

test:
  files:
    - SSLTest.cmake
  commands:
    - cmake --version
    - cmake -V -P SSLTest.cmake
    - ctest --version
    - cpack --version

about:
  home: http://www.cmake.org/
  license: BSD 3-clause
  license_family: BSD
  summary: CMake is an extensible, open-source system that manages the build process

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - blowekamp
    - groutr
    - jakirkham
    - jschueller
    - ocefpaf
    - msarahan
    - scopatz
    - tadeu
    - marcelotrevisani
